WEBVTT

00:11.360 --> 00:14.050
Don't you worry too
much about me, Sis.

00:14.050 --> 00:16.080
No, I'm sure I'll find
work soon as the economy

00:16.080 --> 00:17.880
gets back in the hole.

00:17.880 --> 00:19.510
No, no, I appreciate the
invitation but I'm going

00:19.510 --> 00:20.790
to stay right here in town.

00:20.790 --> 00:24.170
The factory is going
to re-open, you'll see.

00:24.170 --> 00:25.610
Yeah, yeah.

00:25.610 --> 00:29.460
Look, I've got to get back to
my taxes, much as I hate them.

00:29.460 --> 00:32.330
Yeah, all right, love you too.

00:32.330 --> 00:33.270
Yeah, bye.

00:36.100 --> 00:37.780
Welcome to HulkoTax.

00:37.780 --> 00:40.600
A-are you salaried
or self-employed?

00:40.600 --> 00:42.780
Well, I was working at the
toaster factory 'til march,

00:42.780 --> 00:44.680
but since the layoffs I've
been driving for Uber, so--

00:44.680 --> 00:48.340
Enter all W-2s and 1099s.

00:48.340 --> 00:49.310
Oh, OK.

00:49.310 --> 00:50.500
Well, which do I--

00:50.500 --> 00:54.170
Now enter double
2U's at 9 tendy tens.

00:54.170 --> 00:55.960
Well, does the
bank send you that?

00:55.960 --> 00:58.830
Do you have any
commercial fishing income?

00:58.830 --> 00:59.530
I wish.

00:59.530 --> 01:02.180
You have done every
part of this incorrectly.

01:02.180 --> 01:04.260
Now entering manual mode.

01:04.260 --> 01:06.010
Hope you like math,
math, math, math--

01:06.010 --> 01:07.300
Oh, come on!

01:07.300 --> 01:09.010
Why do taxes have to be so hard?

01:09.010 --> 01:12.920
Actually, taxes don't
have to be hard at all.

01:12.920 --> 01:14.370
- Did I kill a man?
- Nope.

01:14.370 --> 01:17.990
You summoned a TV host.

01:17.990 --> 01:21.880
Hi, I'm Adam Conover and this
is Adam Ruins Everything.

01:21.880 --> 01:25.320
[THEME MUSIC]

01:32.780 --> 01:34.540
Man, you scared
the fudge out of me.

01:34.540 --> 01:35.530
Oh, that's nothing.

01:35.530 --> 01:37.960
One time I made my
friend Emily give birth.

01:37.960 --> 01:39.670
I don't know what that
means, but I hate it.

01:39.670 --> 01:41.080
Almost as much as I do my taxes.

01:41.080 --> 01:43.300
Now, what's that you were saying
about how taxes could be easy?

01:43.300 --> 01:44.860
Well, think about it.

01:44.860 --> 01:48.070
Taxes are a bill the
government charges you.

01:48.070 --> 01:50.740
So why do you have
to do all the math?

01:50.740 --> 01:53.600
Imagine if we did that
with any other bill?

01:53.600 --> 01:54.400
How much do I owe you?

01:54.400 --> 01:56.290
You tell me.

01:56.290 --> 01:59.700
Divide number of toppings
by cheese consumption. $12?

01:59.700 --> 02:02.670
Wrong.
Now you're going to jail.

02:02.670 --> 02:05.860
Instead of making you fill
out a complicated return,

02:05.860 --> 02:08.490
why doesn't the government
just tell you how much you owe?

02:08.490 --> 02:09.660
Well, because
they'd need to know

02:09.660 --> 02:11.410
my income, my interest
on my savings,

02:11.410 --> 02:13.000
all the numbers that
are on those forms.

02:13.000 --> 02:15.430
News flash, they already do.

02:15.430 --> 02:18.120
Employers, banks, and other
financial institutions

02:18.120 --> 02:21.110
already send detailed
records to the IRS.

02:21.110 --> 02:24.670
OK, we just got
Hank's W-2s and 1099s.

02:24.670 --> 02:27.920
I could calculate
his tax bill myself.

02:27.920 --> 02:30.130
Nah, I'll just wait
quietly while he sends

02:30.130 --> 02:32.380
me the exact same information.

02:32.380 --> 02:34.300
The government
could, quite literally,

02:34.300 --> 02:36.250
do your taxes for you.

02:36.250 --> 02:38.980
It's an idea called
return free filing.

02:38.980 --> 02:40.870
Instead of the government
checking your work,

02:40.870 --> 02:42.460
you'd check theirs.

02:42.460 --> 02:45.670
And it would make taxes
look more like this.

02:45.670 --> 02:48.640
Oh, honey, our taxes came.

02:48.640 --> 02:52.670
Just need to deduct that work
trip to Toledo and we're done.

02:52.670 --> 02:54.790
Hey, think we have time for
some wild, bedpost rattling

02:54.790 --> 02:56.270
sex?
- Why not?

02:56.270 --> 02:58.200
Our April is wide open.

02:58.200 --> 03:00.910
Return free filing is
already used by countries

03:00.910 --> 03:03.700
around the world and could
allow millions of Americans

03:03.700 --> 03:07.660
like you to do your taxes for
free in just five minutes.

03:07.660 --> 03:09.520
Yeah, well, those
bozos in Washington

03:09.520 --> 03:11.470
would never go for an idea
that makes that much sense.

03:11.470 --> 03:14.020
Actually, return free
filing bills are introduced

03:14.020 --> 03:17.860
in Congress all the time and
both Barack Obama and Ronald

03:17.860 --> 03:19.240
Reagan pushed for it.

03:19.240 --> 03:20.470
Yes we can.

03:20.470 --> 03:25.180
Tear down this
wall of paperwork.

03:25.180 --> 03:26.320
Wow.

03:26.320 --> 03:28.250
That must be the only thing
those guys would agree on.

03:28.250 --> 03:29.910
OK, I'm sold.

03:29.910 --> 03:31.450
Give me return free filing.

03:31.450 --> 03:32.380
Sorry.

03:32.380 --> 03:35.830
The makers of tax software
like TurboTax and H&amp;R Block

03:35.830 --> 03:39.070
spend a boatload of money to
make sure it never happens.

03:41.920 --> 03:44.550
Tax software
industry, you play

03:44.550 --> 03:46.670
us to make your taxes easier.

03:46.670 --> 03:50.260
So we pay lobbyists to make
sure they stay complicated.

03:50.260 --> 03:53.500
Citizens, we feel your pain.

03:53.500 --> 03:56.950
Filing your taxes
is just too darn--

03:56.950 --> 03:57.730
fun.

03:57.730 --> 03:58.660
Everything's great.

03:58.660 --> 04:00.750
We're changing nothing.

04:00.750 --> 04:01.750
Ooh.

04:01.750 --> 04:03.550
These calculating
companies have

04:03.550 --> 04:05.890
lobbied to kill
multiple returns filing

04:05.890 --> 04:08.080
bills over the past decade.

04:08.080 --> 04:10.310
And they're using
my money to do it.

04:10.310 --> 04:11.530
Well, that's shameless.

04:11.530 --> 04:13.480
And it gets worse.

04:13.480 --> 04:16.290
This is Jessica Huseman,
a reporter at ProPublica

04:16.290 --> 04:17.560
who's covered this story.

04:17.560 --> 04:20.560
The tax prep industry
actually created a front group

04:20.560 --> 04:22.510
called the FreeFile
Alliance that lets

04:22.510 --> 04:24.580
you file your taxes for free.

04:24.580 --> 04:28.090
It's supposed to be available
to 2/3 of the taxpaying public,

04:28.090 --> 04:30.370
but almost no one uses it.

04:30.370 --> 04:32.440
That's because the
system is confusing,

04:32.440 --> 04:35.860
the IRS doesn't market it, the
tax companies have no incentive

04:35.860 --> 04:39.010
to push it themselves,
and a sneaky opt in option

04:39.010 --> 04:41.470
allows them to push
their paid products.

04:41.470 --> 04:44.320
Don't use the free
option it's too hard.

04:44.320 --> 04:45.790
Pay me instead.

04:45.790 --> 04:48.550
But I want return free filing
like you were talking about.

04:48.550 --> 04:50.080
Well, here's the worst part.

04:50.080 --> 04:52.840
The tax industry negotiated
an exclusive deal

04:52.840 --> 04:55.750
that prevents the federal
government from offering return

04:55.750 --> 04:59.360
free filing or any free
system of tax filing

04:59.360 --> 05:02.140
so long as the FreeFile
Alliance exists.

05:02.140 --> 05:04.120
So you're saying the
government could do my taxes

05:04.120 --> 05:06.880
for me for free,
but TurboTax and H&amp;R

05:06.880 --> 05:08.800
Block are working like crazy
to stop that from happening?

05:08.800 --> 05:09.910
Exactly.

05:09.910 --> 05:14.110
Instead, you're stuck doing your
taxes yourself with this guy.

05:14.110 --> 05:16.080
Get ready to spend all
your Aprils with me--

05:16.080 --> 05:16.780
me.

05:19.510 --> 05:21.490
See, this is the
problem with the economy.

05:21.490 --> 05:22.910
The government and
the CEOs getting rich,

05:22.910 --> 05:24.340
and the rest of us get
screwed by something

05:24.340 --> 05:25.840
takes three degrees
to understand.

05:25.840 --> 05:28.620
Yeah, you pretty
much nailed it.

05:28.620 --> 05:30.730
See, that's why
I like this guy.

05:30.730 --> 05:33.140
Bad news coming
in from Wall Street.

05:33.140 --> 05:36.010
The Dow is down 500 points,
which means we're heading

05:36.010 --> 05:39.590
into the icy depths of poverty.

05:39.590 --> 05:41.280
Joe "Cray Cray" Crazawitz.

05:41.280 --> 05:43.130
He makes the economy so simple.

05:43.130 --> 05:44.260
Yeah, he does.

05:44.260 --> 05:46.390
And that's what
makes him so wrong.

05:46.390 --> 05:47.870
I'll show you.

05:47.870 --> 05:49.500
Hey, don't come
into a man's house

05:49.500 --> 05:52.100
and teleport him
against his will.

05:52.100 --> 05:54.600
[DOG WHINING]

05:58.600 --> 06:00.030
[BOXING BELL RINGING]

06:00.030 --> 06:02.790
Welcome back to Demented
Dollars, America's loudest

06:02.790 --> 06:05.360
and therefore best
financial advice show.

06:05.360 --> 06:08.450
The Dow Jones Industrial
Average is down in the dumps,

06:08.450 --> 06:10.650
just like me after every date.

06:10.650 --> 06:11.980
MAN: I think we should
see other people.

06:11.980 --> 06:14.430
And that means the
economy is ruined.

06:14.430 --> 06:16.100
So, it's time to panic.

06:16.100 --> 06:17.230
[SCREAMING]

06:17.230 --> 06:19.100
Actually, No it isn't.

06:19.100 --> 06:21.740
The American economy is
an incredibly complicated

06:21.740 --> 06:25.520
system that even experts spend
a lifetime trying to understand.

06:25.520 --> 06:27.610
So when the news media
dumbs it all down

06:27.610 --> 06:29.990
into how a single
number changed that day,

06:29.990 --> 06:32.000
it tells you a lot
less than you think.

06:32.000 --> 06:33.000
Who the heck are you?

06:33.000 --> 06:34.300
Hi, name's Hank.

06:34.300 --> 06:35.520
Big fan Mr. Crazawitz.

06:35.520 --> 06:36.460
Can I call you Cray Cray?

06:36.460 --> 06:38.110
And can you tell him
that he's full of it?

06:38.110 --> 06:40.030
The Dow tells us how the
whole stock market is doing.

06:40.030 --> 06:40.730
Nope.

06:40.730 --> 06:44.000
It tells you how a tiny part
of the stock market is doing,

06:44.000 --> 06:46.820
and its methodology
is deeply flawed.

06:46.820 --> 06:51.140
The US stock market is an
enormous system with over 3,000

06:51.140 --> 06:53.800
publicly traded companies
in the US alone,

06:53.800 --> 06:56.520
but the Dow includes
just 30 of them.

06:56.520 --> 06:59.810
And it's basically designed
to go up over time.

06:59.810 --> 07:03.320
If a stock does do poorly,
it gets dropped and replaced.

07:03.320 --> 07:04.500
What?

07:04.500 --> 07:05.670
You mean the whole
thing is rigged?

07:05.670 --> 07:08.150
Yup, and it's not
adjusted for inflation.

07:08.150 --> 07:09.530
MAN: Yeah-- yeah-- yeah-- right.

07:09.530 --> 07:11.750
Well if that were true,
then how come all of us

07:11.750 --> 07:14.540
in the media report
on it constantly?

07:14.540 --> 07:15.830
Maybe because
that's what you've

07:15.830 --> 07:17.930
been doing for a century.

07:17.930 --> 07:20.990
See, the Dow became popular
during the economic panics

07:20.990 --> 07:23.360
and depressions of
the early 20th century

07:23.360 --> 07:25.410
when people were
desperate for any sign

07:25.410 --> 07:27.200
of how the economy was doing.

07:27.200 --> 07:28.890
Are we ruined or ain't we?

07:28.890 --> 07:31.420
I just need some kind of sign.

07:31.420 --> 07:35.300
There's the Dow, and
it's just gone bust.

07:35.300 --> 07:36.230
Thanks.

07:36.230 --> 07:39.290
Guess it's curtains for me.

07:39.290 --> 07:41.360
Now, back when our
economy was simpler,

07:41.360 --> 07:43.070
the performance of
30 big companies

07:43.070 --> 07:45.260
was actually pretty
useful information.

07:45.260 --> 07:47.900
But as our economy grew
and became more complex,

07:47.900 --> 07:50.420
the Dow started to
tell us less and less.

07:50.420 --> 07:54.120
And today, financial insiders
don't even pay attention to it.

07:54.120 --> 07:55.060
Dude, don't jump.

07:55.060 --> 07:55.990
The Dow is like, sick.

07:55.990 --> 07:57.710
It's like up 1,000 points.

07:57.710 --> 07:59.900
Who cares about that
meaningless number?

07:59.900 --> 08:04.340
My wife cheated on me
with a pottery instructor.

08:04.340 --> 08:07.400
Hey, please don't
make light of suicide.

08:07.400 --> 08:08.230
It's insensitive.

08:08.230 --> 08:09.430
Sorry.

08:09.430 --> 08:12.850
Today, despite the fact that
the Dow tells us less than ever,

08:12.850 --> 08:16.360
reporters like Cray Cray keep
using it out of sheer habit.

08:16.360 --> 08:19.750
Yeah, well, I have another
habit: doing my show.

08:19.750 --> 08:20.840
You two done?

08:20.840 --> 08:25.200
Because it's time
for the job's report!

08:25.200 --> 08:28.320
I know I was just screaming
that the economy is doomed,

08:28.320 --> 08:30.730
but it's actually great
because the employment

08:30.730 --> 08:34.120
rate is down to 4.5%.
[WHISTLE]

08:34.120 --> 08:36.880
So 96% of folks
are making a living?

08:36.880 --> 08:37.900
That's great.
ADAM CONOVER (VOICEOVER): A--

08:37.900 --> 08:38.880
A-- Actually--

08:38.880 --> 08:42.210
The number you hear reported
as the unemployment rate is--

08:42.210 --> 08:43.640
ADAM CONOVER (VOICEOVER):
The female hymen.

08:43.640 --> 08:45.480
