Old episode.

08:45.480 --> 08:48.120
The unemployment rate
is a flawed number

08:48.120 --> 08:50.430
that excludes tons of
people who you and I

08:50.430 --> 08:51.840
would consider unemployed.

08:51.840 --> 08:53.070
Well, I find that
hard to believe.

08:53.070 --> 08:54.270
You're either working
or you're not.

08:54.270 --> 08:56.610
Well, let's play America's
least favorite game

08:56.610 --> 08:58.920
show, Who Counts As Unemployed?

08:58.920 --> 08:59.630
[APPLAUSE]

08:59.630 --> 09:01.710
Up first, we have Trista.

09:01.710 --> 09:02.520
I'm 24.

09:02.520 --> 09:04.180
I got laid off a few months ago.

09:04.180 --> 09:07.680
And I've been so depressed
that I haven't looked for work.

09:07.680 --> 09:08.510
She's unemployed.

09:08.510 --> 09:09.210
[BUZZER]

09:09.210 --> 09:10.980
Not according
to the government.

09:10.980 --> 09:12.210
Hi, I'm Charles.

09:12.210 --> 09:13.410
I'm 52.

09:13.410 --> 09:17.310
And this week I mowed my
neighbor's lawn for $25.

09:17.310 --> 09:20.470
That's-- that's all the
work I've had in months.

09:20.470 --> 09:22.150
Well, he must
count as unemployed.

09:22.150 --> 09:24.120
[BUZZER]
- No again.

09:24.120 --> 09:25.870
And finally, we have Hank.

09:25.870 --> 09:26.740
Me?

09:26.740 --> 09:29.350
Well, I drive Uber some nights
since the factory closed.

09:29.350 --> 09:31.140
But I'm barely making by.
I'm unemployed.

09:31.140 --> 09:31.880
[BUZZER]

09:31.880 --> 09:32.760
Wrong again.

09:32.760 --> 09:33.840
You don't count either.

09:33.840 --> 09:35.970
Thanks for playing and
remember to spell and grammar

09:35.970 --> 09:37.470
check your resume.

09:37.470 --> 09:38.820
Why don't I count
as unemployed?

09:38.820 --> 09:40.560
Well, the number
we always hear

09:40.560 --> 09:44.040
reported as the unemployment
rate only counts people who

09:44.040 --> 09:46.200
are actively looking
for work and excludes

09:46.200 --> 09:49.590
anyone who's earned more
than $20 in the past week.

09:49.590 --> 09:51.510
Now, that doesn't make
it totally useless

09:51.510 --> 09:53.850
but if you hear that number and
think that's how many people

09:53.850 --> 09:55.500
are out of work, you're wrong.

09:55.500 --> 09:56.970
Many more are struggling.

09:56.970 --> 09:58.800
Yeah, like me.

09:58.800 --> 10:01.080
That's enough for bloated
Anderson Cooper here.

10:01.080 --> 10:03.150
Time to whip out the big guns.

10:03.150 --> 10:04.510
Let's talk G--

10:04.510 --> 10:05.980
[HORN]
