10:05.980 --> 10:07.250
[HORN]
P.

10:07.250 --> 10:08.440
[HORN]
- Yes!

10:08.440 --> 10:09.430
GDP!

10:09.430 --> 10:11.020
The bigger it gets,
the better the economy

10:11.020 --> 10:11.770
is, right Cray Cray?

10:11.770 --> 10:12.850
Absolutely!

10:12.850 --> 10:15.090
Let's take a look at
the latest figure--

10:15.090 --> 10:15.880
Sorry.

10:15.880 --> 10:19.600
Even though politicians and
the media act like GDP--

10:19.600 --> 10:21.520
or gross domestic product--

10:21.520 --> 10:25.210
is a measure of our overall
economic well-being, it ain't.

10:25.210 --> 10:27.640
GDP really only tells
us how much we make

10:27.640 --> 10:29.080
and how much we consume.

10:29.080 --> 10:31.960
In other words, it goes
up when spending does.

10:31.960 --> 10:33.310
I got a raise.

10:33.310 --> 10:35.350
I'm going to buy a catamaran.

10:35.350 --> 10:37.520
That's good for me, Mr. GDP.

10:37.520 --> 10:41.740
But the problem is, spending
isn't always a good thing.

10:41.740 --> 10:44.510
GDP could also go up because
something bad happened

10:44.510 --> 10:47.260
and we had to spend
money to fix it.

10:47.260 --> 10:48.850
My house was
destroyed in a hurricane

10:48.850 --> 10:51.010
so I need to buy a
tent to sleep in.

10:51.010 --> 10:52.270
Here's all my savings.

10:52.270 --> 10:55.860
All spending is good
spending for Mr. GDP.

10:55.860 --> 10:57.780
But she lost her
house and her savings.

10:57.780 --> 10:59.470
That can't be good
for the economy.

10:59.470 --> 11:02.540
No, but she spent
money so GDP goes up.

11:02.540 --> 11:04.390
I thought when GDP rose
that meant things were

11:04.390 --> 11:05.580
getting better for everybody?

11:05.580 --> 11:09.310
Sadly, a strong GDP doesn't
guarantee the average person

11:09.310 --> 11:10.960
feels any benefit.

11:10.960 --> 11:14.350
In the last two decades GDP has
steadily risen, but the average

11:14.350 --> 11:16.240
American's earnings haven't.

11:16.240 --> 11:19.660
It's actually possible to have
the highest GDP and the most

11:19.660 --> 11:21.470
poverty at the same time.
